Iavan Pijoos, News24Durban &ndash; A 51-year-old man was shot when he interrupted a house robbery in Umgeni Park, Durban, paramedics said on Friday. &nbsp; Netcare911 spokesperson Chris Botha said a house robbery was in progress and when a neighbour came out of his house to investigate he was shot and seriously wounded.Botha said paramedics found the man lying on the ground in a serious condition.He was stabilised&nbsp;and taken to a nearby hospital.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.